    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-19T12:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-19T12:36:00-05:00" n="978"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d978">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14053.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-19T11:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>241. Had very cordial conference this morning with General Gutiérrez to whom I
                    delivered a translation of yours December 16, 1914, 4 p.m., No. 360. I added
                    adequate remarks impressing upon him the convenience of carrying out your
                    suggestion. He stated that he was in complete accord with them and authorized me
                    to assure you that he and his Cabinet have now for days been treating the
                    question of general amnesty with great hopes of arriving at a satisfactory
                    solution. He also told me that the Government is greatly interested in relieving
                    the financial situation and will try to meet the payments of Dublic debts as far
                    as possible even at the sacrifice of <pb facs="0750" n="634" xml:id="pg_634"/>
                    the pay of its own army. He promised to reply in writing to the other points
                    contained in your message.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
